<hr width="100%" size="2">
<h1><i><a name="iocmd"></a><font color="#0000aa">iocmd.jar</font></i></h1>

<p>
<b>Description</b><br>
This bundle provides a front-end command (for OSCAR shell) to write message in a open connection<br>
For more details on how to use this bundle, refer to the /doc/readme.html file embedded in the bundle jarfile and to iosender.jar embedded documentation.<br>
</p>

<p>
<b>Contributors</b><br>
Didier Donsez (<a href="mailto:Didier.Donsez@ieee.org">Didier.Donsez@ieee.org</a>)<br>
</p>

<p>
<b>License</b><br>
LGPL<br>
</p>

<p>
<b>Services</b><br>
<code>org.ungoverned.oscar.service.shell.Command</code>
</p>

<p>
<b>Properties</b><br>
None<br>
</p>

<p><b>Requirements</b><br>
1 <code>org.osgi.service.io.ConnectorService</code><br>
servicebinder.jar<br>
</p>

<!-- End of OSCAR Bundle Documentation -->

<hr width="100%" size="2">

<!-- Start of extra information  -->

<p>
<b>Download</b><br>
<ul>
<li><a href='http://www-adele.imag.fr/~donsez/dev/osgi/iocmd/iocmd.jar'>Bundle binaries</a></li>
<li><a href='http://www-adele.imag.fr/~donsez/dev/osgi/iocmd/iocmd-src.jar'>Bundle sources</a></li>
<li><a href='http://www-adele.imag.fr/~donsez/dev/osgi/iocmd/readme.html'>The latest version of this documentation</a></li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>
<b>Build</b><br>
<ol>
<li>configure the build properties in build.xml</li>
<li>then build with ant</li>
</ol>
</p>

<p>
<b>Usage</b><br>
add a command <code>io</code> in the OSCAR shell
<pre>
io mail://me@mycomp.com?SUBJECT=Test This is a MAIL scheme test
io sms://+33612345678 This is also a SMS scheme test
</pre>

</p>

<p>
<b>Tested gateways</b><br>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://oscar.objectweb.org/">OSCAR</a></li>
</ul>
</p>

